body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to CarBiz Support. My name is Jack Alexander. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Amy Campbell.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Amy. How can I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling confused about the security measures at your dealership.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand. To assist you better, could you provide me with your phone number, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five, one two three, four five six seven.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Amy. And, could you also provide me with your home address?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's two zero zero, Main Street, Cityville, State ABC, Zip Code one zero zero zero one.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Amy. I will assist you with your security concerns. I appreciate your time.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time. Have a great day, Amy. Goodbye.
